name: Generic Command Injection Vulnerability Scanner
mini_desc: A command injection vulnerability occurs when an attacker is able to pass malicious input to a program and have that input executed as an OS command. This can allow attackers to run operation system-level command execution. Command injection is often possible due to insecure coding practices that do not properly validate or sanitize user input.
meta_title: Command Injection Vulnerability Scanner

name: Generic CRLF Injection Vulnerability Scanner
mini_desc: The CRLF (\r\n) abbreviation refers to Carriage Return and Line Feed. A CRLF injection attack is a type of injection attack that exploits the combination of a carriage return and line feed characters, which are used to end a line of text in a file or command.
meta_title: CRLF Vulnerability Scanner

name: Generic CSRF Vulnerability Scanner
mini_desc: Cross-Site Request Forgery, also known as CSRF is an attack vector that tricks a web browser into sending malicious requests to a web application on behalf of the user that is currently authenticated. These requests can perform any action that the user is authorized to do, such as changing their password, making purchases, or posting comments.
meta_title: Online CSRF Vulnerability Scanner

name: Generic SSRF vulnerability scanner
mini_desc:
Server-side request forgery (SSRF), is a vulnerability that allows an attacker to execute unauthorized requests from the perspective of the webserver. SSRF can be used to access sensitive data, such as internal network resources and user data, or to launch attacks on other systems from the webserver.

The impact of SSRF attacks can be significant. They can allow attackers to arbitrary command execution, access internal apps, and even scan ports in the local network.
meta_title: Online SSRF vulnerability scanner

name: Generic Open Redirect Vulnerability Scanner
mini_desc: An Open Redirect Vulnerability is a  type of vulnerability that can occur in web applications. It is a weakness that takes advantage of a flaw in the application's design or coding, which allows an attacker to redirect a user to a malicious website.
meta_title: Online Open Redirect Vulnerability Scanner

name: Generic XXE Vulnerability Scanner
mini_desc: XML external entity injection (also known as XXE) is a vulnerability that can be exploited by attackers to read and write files on the target server, as well as access sensitive data. XXE is a type of injection attack that occurs when an attacker injects XML input into an application that uses XML processing. This can allow the attacker to access files on the server and even execute arbitrary code.
meta_title: Online XXE Vulnerability Scanner

name: Online Generic File Inclusion - LFI/RFI Vulnerability Scanner
mini_desc: File inclusion vulnerabilities are a type of vulnerability that occurs when an attacker is able to include a file, usually through using inputs on the webserver. These vulnerabilities can lead to information disclosure, arbitrary code execution, and full system compromise.
meta_title: Online File Inclusion - LFI/RFI Vulnerability Scanner

name: Free and Online Generic XSS Scanner
